title: about
text:
My research is broadly focused on the delivery of youth mental health services. This work is guided by frameworks from public health (MTSS; Collaborative Care) and implementation science (EPIS; NPT). Specific interest include:

Advancing the integration youth mental health services in school, hospital, and primary care settings.
Investigating contextual factors that influence how professionals and organizations implement evidence-based mental health services while de-implementing low value practices.
Identifying inequities to access to mental health services.

My methodological interests include quantitative methods using the R statistical software, mixed-methods, and improving the translation of research into practice through meta-science and reproducibility.
